# Benin Insights — Non-Negotiable Standards

- Apply `.github/copilot-instructions.md` for every coding task in this repo.
- Keep changes small, explicit, reviewable, and reproducible.
- Prefer pure functions, explicit contracts, and boundary validation.
- Fail fast on invalid state; never silently ignore missing/invalid data.
- Do not return `None` for failure paths; use explicit exceptions.
- Keep orchestration thin; place business logic in proper model/domain layers.
- Avoid speculative abstractions (YAGNI); abstract only after repetition (DRY).
- Use simplest implementation that satisfies `docs/ml_specs.md`.
- Keep scripts idempotent and avoid hardcoded paths/settings.
- Update `docs/ml_todo.md` whenever ML scope/tasks evolve.

# Delivery Discipline

- Order of work: working code -> green tests -> cleanup.
- Keep repository outputs reproducible and easy for next contributors.
